ter he understands more and more clearly the evil that is still left in him. When a man is getting worse, he understands his own badness less and less.\n\n- C.S. Lewis, Mere Christianity\n|\nPlenty of people who survive tragedies end up ambivalent about danger--frightened by it, yet strangely drawn to it.\n\n- Keith Ablow, Denial\n|\nThe mind is weak, and it must be mastered, controlled. The body, it knows no master save for instinct and, unfortunately, it is built for terminal suffering.\n\n- Jennifer Arnett, Day One: A Novella\n|\nWe all know in our mind what we want, but nobody know exactly what we Get.\n\n- Jan\n|\n...In this place you could not feel anything, except pain and foreknowledge of pain.\n\n- George Orwell, 1984\n|\nMother Earth has never been more crowded, yet her inhabitants have never been more lonely.\n\n- Anasazi\n|\nIf we break someone’s ego, then we can’t be happy. Egoism is his life!\n\n- Dada\n|\nWe pay for sins we do not remember, and seek to do a will we can scarce fathom. That is what it is, to be a god's chosen.\n\n- Jacqueline Carey, Kushiel's Avatar\n|\nDon't fear mistakes, they are your stepping stone to success\n\n- Bangambiki Habyarimana, The Great Pearl of Wisdom\n|\nWe’ (the Gnani Purush, the enlightened one) do not have the time to prove that ‘ours’ is correct; nor do ‘we’ have the time to make you correct as well.\n\n- Dada\n|\nIt is certain that we cannot escape anguish, for we are anguish.\n\n- Jean-Paul Sartre, Being and Nothingness\n|\nWhen our government is spoken of as some menacing, threatening foreign entity, it ignores the fact that, in our democracy, government is us.\n\n- Barack\n|\nFear triggers need, need powers sincerity. Sincerity is the required element.\n\n- Terry Goodkind, The First Confessor\n|\nShe craved a family, not having had enough of one to understand what a pain in the ass it was.\n\n- Maile Meloy, Both Ways is the Only Way I Want It\n|\nAll have some artificial badge which the world, and themselves among the first, learn to consider as a genuine characteristic.\n\n- Nathaniel Hawthorne, Mosses from an Old Manse\n|\nKing die hard, in Shakespeare and in life.\n\n- Harold Bloom, The Western Canon: The Books and School of the Ages\n|\nMind is like a net, drawn by the needles of past and future. Mindfulness is the way for not getting stuck into that net.\n\n- Amit Ray, Mindfulness Living in the Moment - Living in the Breath\n|\nFor me, every week is a fashion week.\n\n- Nuno\n|\nI am not a broken heart,and I am not your fault.\n\n- Charlotte Eriksson, You're Doing Just Fine\n|\nThis is your karma. You do not understand now, but you will understand later. The source of pain is within your own larger expression of being.\n\n- H. Raven Rose, Shadow Selves: Double Happiness\n|\nYou can begin to dream, to love, to dance, to read, to sing, to study, to paint, to teach, to draw, to swim, to exercise, to write….!\n\n- Lailah Gifty Akita, Think Great: Be Great!"